summary: This module provides lang library operations on float values defined by the language specification 2020R1.
description:
Module Overview

This module provides lang library operations on float values defined by the language specification 2020R1.

functions.name: abs
functions.description: IEEE abs operation.

functions.name: acos
functions.description: Returns the arccosine of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE acos operation

functions.name: asin
functions.description: Returns the arcsine of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE asin operation.

functions.name: atan
functions.description: Returns the arctangent of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE atan operation.

returnParameters.description: the angle in radians from the positive x-axis to the point whose Cartesian coordinates are (x, y)

functions.name: atan2
functions.description: Performs the 2-argument arctangent operation. Corresponds IEEE atan2(y, x) operation.

functions.name: cbrt
functions.description: Returns the cube root of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE rootn(x, 3) operation.

returnParameters.description: smallest (closest to -∞) decimal value not less than x that is a mathematical integer

functions.name: ceiling
functions.description: Rounds a float up to the closest integral value.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: float value, specifying an angle in radians

functions.name: cos
functions.description: Returns the cosine of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE cos operation.

functions.name: cosh
functions.description: Returns the hyperbolic cosine of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE cosh operation.

functions.name: exp
functions.description: Raises Euler's number to a power. Corresponds to IEEE exp operation.

returnParameters.description: largest (closest to +∞) float value not greater than x that is a mathematical integer.

functions.name: floor
functions.description: Rounds a float down to the closest integral value.

functions.name: fromBitsInt
functions.description: Returns the float that is represented in IEEE 64-bit floating point by x. All bit patterns that IEEE defines to be NaNs will all be mapped to the single float NaN value.

functions.name: fromHexString
functions.description:
Return the float value represented by s. s must follow the syntax of HexFloatingPointLiteral as defined by the Ballerina specification with the following modifications

  • the HexFloatingPointLiteral may have a leading + or - sign
  • NaN is allowed
  • Infinity is allowed with an optional leading + or - sign

functions.name: fromString
functions.description:
Return the float value represented by s. s must follow the syntax of DecimalFloatingPointNumber as defined by the Ballerina specification with the following modifications

  • the DecimalFloatingPointNumber may have a leading + or - sign
  • NaN is allowed
  • Infinity is allowed with an optional leading + or - sign
  • a FloatingPointTypeSuffix is not allowed This is the inverse of value:toString applied to an float.

returnParameters.description: true if x is finite, i.e. neither NaN nor +∞ nor -∞

functions.name: isFinite
functions.description: Tests whether a float is finite. Exactly one of isFinite, isInfinite and IsNaN will be true for any float value

functions.name: isInfinite
functions.description: Tests whether a float is infinite. Exactly one of isFinite, isInfinite and IsNaN will be true for any float value

functions.name: isNaN
functions.description: Tests whether a float is NaN. Exactly one of isFinite, isInfinite and IsNaN will be true for any float value.

functions.name: log
functions.description: Returns the natural logarithm of a float value Corresponds to IEEE log operation.

functions.name: log10
functions.description: Returns the base 10 logarithm of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE log10 operation.

functions.name: max
functions.description: Maximum of zero or more float values. Result is -∞ if no args NaN if any arg is NaN

functions.name: min
functions.description: Minimum of zero or more float values. Result is +∞ if no args Result is NaN if any arg is NaN

functions.name: pow
functions.description: Raises one float value to the power of another float values. Corresponds to IEEE pow(x, y) operation.

returnParameters.description: closest float value to x that is a mathematical integer

functions.name: round
functions.description: Round a float value to the closest integral value. Returns the float value that is a mathematical integer and closest to x. If there are two such values, choose the one that is even (this is the round-to-nearest rounding mode, which is the default for IEEE and for Ballerina). Same as Java Math.rint method Same as .NET Math.Round method IEEE roundToIntegralTiesToEven operation Note that <int>x is the same as <int>x.round()

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: float value, specifying an angle in radians

functions.name: sin
functions.description: Returns the sine of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE sin operation.

functions.name: sinh
functions.description: Returns the hyperbolic sine of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE sinh operation.

functions.name: sqrt
functions.description: Returns the square root of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE squareRoot operation.

returnParameters.description: sum of all the xs, +0.0 if xs is empty

functions.name: sum
functions.description: Sum of zero or more float values. Result is NaN if any arg is NaN

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: float value, specifying an angle in radians

functions.name: tan
functions.description: Returns the tangent of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE tan operation

functions.name: tanh
functions.description: Returns the hyperbolic tangent of a float value. Corresponds to IEEE tanh operation.

functions.name: toBitsInt
functions.description: Returns IEEE 64-bit binary floating point format representation of x as an int.

functions.name: toHexString
functions.description:
Returns a string that represents x as a hexadecimal floating point number. The returned string will comply to the grammar of HexFloatingPointLiteral in the Ballerina spec with the following modifications:

  • it will have a leading - sign if negative
  • positive infinity will be represented by Infinity
  • negative infinity will be represented by -Infinity
  • NaN will be represented by NaN The representation includes 0x for finite numbers.
